2.1 Installing Goblins
======================

You’ll need to install ‘guile-goblins’.  Either use Guix
(https://guix.gnu.org/) or use your standard GNU/Linux distro’s package
for ‘guile-goblins’ (if it exists), or even better yet run Guix as your
standard distro.

   Otherwise see the ‘HACKING’ and ‘README’ files with git checkouts /
release tarballs to install.


File: goblins.info,  Node: Setup for hacking on Goblins,  Next: TEMPORARY Live hacking ``fix'',  Prev: Installing Goblins,  Up: Getting started

2.2 Setup for hacking on Goblins
================================

You’re going to want/need:

   • GNU Emacs (https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/)
   • Geiser (https://www.nongnu.org/geiser/), for hacking on Guile

   Then, at minimum, you’ll want to put in your .emacs:

     (show-paren-mode 1)  ; Match parentheses

   However you probably also want some combination of:

   • smartparens (https://github.com/Fuco1/smartparens) (or paredit
     (https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/ParEdit), which is much more
     strict... use smartparens if uncertain)
   • rainbow-delimiters (https://github.com/Fanael/rainbow-delimiters)
   • highlight-parentheses
     (https://www.emacswiki.org/emacs/HighlightParentheses)

   Now you’ll have a nice hacking setup!  Be sure to read the Geiser
manual.


