6.3 Facet
=========

The ‘(goblins actor-lib facet)’ module provides an actor to wrap another
object and only allow certain methods through.  It also provides a
convenience function for constructing such actors.

 -- Constructor: ^facet bcom wrap-me [methods ...]

     Construct a proxy of the actor WRAP-ME with access to only METHODS,
     a list of symbols corresponding to methods of WRAP-ME.  The WRAP-ME
     will be invoked with ‘$’ if possible, and otherwise will be invoked
     with ‘<-’.  For cases where synchronicity is possible but not
     desired, invoking the ‘facet’ asynchronously has the same effect as
     invoking WRAP-ME asynchronously.

 -- Procedure: facet wrap-me [methods ...]

     Spawn and return a reference to a ‘^facet’, passing along arguments
     to their equivalents in the constructor.

