7 OCapN: The Object Capabilities Network
****************************************

OCapN (https://github.com/ocapn/ocapn) stands for “Object Capability
Network” and is a suite of protocols for communication between
distributed, networked objects.  In other words, it’s how Goblins actors
can talk to actors running on another computer.

   OCapN uses the Capability Transport Protocol (CapTP)
(http://erights.org/elib/distrib/captp/index.html) as the core protocol
for enabling distributed programming in a mutually suspicious network.
It originated in the E programming language (http://www.erights.org/)
but has since appeared in Cap’N Proto (https://capnproto.org/), Waterken
(http://waterken.sourceforge.net/), Agoric (https://agoric.com/)’s
SwingSet
(https://github.com/Agoric/agoric-sdk/tree/master/packages/SwingSet),
and now Goblins.

   *CAUTION*: CapTP support is still in its early days.  Please do not
rely on the protocol being stable at this time.

* Menu:

* CapTP The Capability Transport Protocol::
* Launching a Tor daemon for Goblins::
* Example Greeters over CapTP via Tor::
* Example Simple chat via TCP-TLS::
* Using the CapTP API::
* Netlayers::
* Handling Disconnects::


