7.6 Netlayers
=============

While OCapN’s CapTP provides the glue of object-to-object remote
invocation machinery, OCapN’s netlayers are an abstraction over message
transmission protocols which give OCapN the flexibility to use a number
of underlying networking substrates.

* Menu:

* Tor Onion Services::
* TCP + TLS::
* Unix domain socket::
* libp2p::
* WebSocket::
* Prelay::
* Prelay Utils::


